# Thinking in Vim

Vim commands follow a grammar: **verb + modifier + noun** (or **operator + count + motion**)

## The Grammar
  ```
  [count] operator [count] motion/text-object
  ```

  | Component      | Examples                    | Description                    |
  |----------------|-----------------------------|--------------------------------|
  | **Operators**  | `d` `c` `y` `v` `>` `<` `=` | what to do (verb)              |
  | **Motions**    | `w` `e` `b` `j` `k` `$` `0` | where to go                    |
  | **Text Obj**   | `iw` `i"` `ap` `iF`         | what to act on (noun)          |
  | **Count**      | `2` `3` `10`                | how many times                 |

## Common Operators (Verbs)
  | Key | Action                     | Mnemonic        |
  |-----|----------------------------|-----------------|
  | `d` | delete (and yank)          | **d**elete      |
  | `c` | change (delete + insert)   | **c**hange      |
  | `y` | yank (copy)                | **y**ank        |
  | `v` | visual select              | **v**isual      |
  | `>` | indent right               |                 |
  | `<` | indent left                |                 |
  | `=` | auto-format                |                 |
  | `g~`| toggle case                |                 |
  | `gu`| lowercase                  |                 |
  | `gU`| uppercase                  |                 |

## Common Motions (Movement)
  | Key     | Motion                     | Mnemonic        |
  |---------|----------------------------|-----------------|
  | `w`     | start of next word         | **w**ord        |
  | `e`     | end of word                | **e**nd         |
  | `b`     | back to start of word      | **b**ack        |
  | `0`     | start of line              | column **0**    |
  | `$`     | end of line                | regex end       |
  | `^`     | first non-blank            |                 |
  | `gg`    | start of file              | **g**o          |
  | `G`     | end of file                |                 |
  | `f{c}`  | forward to char {c}        | **f**ind        |
  | `t{c}`  | forward until char {c}     | un**t**il       |
  | `F{c}`  | backward to char {c}       |                 |
  | `T{c}`  | backward until char {c}    |                 |
  | `;`     | repeat f/t forward         |                 |
  | `,`     | repeat f/t backward        |                 |
  | `%`     | matching bracket           |                 |
  | `{`     | previous blank line        |                 |
  | `}`     | next blank line            |                 |

