## Dot Command (Repeat)
  | Command            | Then `.` repeats              |
  |--------------------|-------------------------------|
  | `ciw` new `<Esc>`  | change word to "new"          |
  | `dd`               | delete line                   |
  | `>>`               | indent line                   |
  | `A;` `<Esc>`       | append semicolon to line      |
  | `daw`              | delete a word                 |

  **Workflow**: Do an edit once, then press `.` to repeat on other locations.
  Use `n` to find next match, `.` to apply same change.

## Common Workflows

  **Change all occurrences of a word:**
  ```
  /word        search for word
  cgn          change next match (auto-selects match)
  new<Esc>     type replacement
  .            repeat on next match
  ```

  **Delete everything inside brackets:**
  ```
  di(          or dip (AZERTY shortcut)
  ```

  **Wrap word in quotes:**
  ```
  saiw"        surround add inner word with "
  ```

  **Change function parameters:**
  ```
  ci(          change inside parentheses
  ```

  **Delete until specific character:**
  ```
  dt,          delete until comma
  df,          delete through comma (includes it)
  ```

  **Copy a function and paste it:**
  ```
  yiF          yank inner function
  p            paste below
  ```

