## Regex Modes
  | Prefix | Mode            | Description                                       |
  |--------|-----------------|---------------------------------------------------|
  | `\v`   | very magic      | most chars special — closest to Perl/Python regex |
  | `\m`   | magic (default) | `.` `*` `[]` `^` `$` are special, rest literal   |
  | `\M`   | no magic        | only `^` and `$` are special                      |
  | `\V`   | very no magic   | nothing special except `\` — pure literal search  |

  **Use `\v` for most patterns, `\V` for literal strings (paths, code with brackets)**

## Regex Examples (very magic `\v`)
  | Pattern                          | Matches                                    |
  |----------------------------------|--------------------------------------------|
  | `/\v(foo\|bar)+`                 | one or more "foo" or "bar"                 |
  | `/\vfunction \w+`                | any function declaration                   |
  | `/\v^\s*$`                       | blank lines (only whitespace)              |
  | `/\v<word>`                      | exact word boundary match                  |
  | `:%s/\v(\w+)\()/\1Args()/g`      | rename all no-arg calls to `Args()` calls  |
  | `:%s/\vconst (\w+) = .+/let \1/g`| strip const assignments to bare `let`     |
  | `/\V./some/path[0]`              | literal search for path with brackets      |

